# AI Context Documentation Rules

The `ai-context/` folder contains project documentation for AI agents.

## Purpose

These files are the single source of truth for project decisions.
These files are committed to git. They are not part of the app runtime — they exist as project documentation for AI agents.

## Rules

- Written in Ukrainian (exception to the English-only rule for code)
- Keep files up to date when making architectural changes
- When adding a new feature module, update `project-structure.md`
- When adding/changing API endpoints, update `api-design.md`
- When modifying DB schemas, update `data-model.md`
- When adding new libraries, update `tech-stack.md`
- When product requirements change, update `app-concept.md`

## File Roles

| File | Updates when... |
|------|----------------|
| `app-concept.md` | Features, hierarchy, or product decisions change |
| `project-structure.md` | New modules, folders, or structure changes |
| `tech-stack.md` | New libraries added or stack decisions change |
| `data-model.md` | MongoDB schemas, indexes, or aggregation logic changes |
| `api-design.md` | API endpoints, request/response contracts change |
